 how sentiment and reason interacted in the eighteenth century to produce not only new kinds of knowledge but new kinds of families as well.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aEnlightenmentzFrance. 0aFamilieszFrancexPhilosophy. 0aPhilosophersxFamily relationshipszFrance. 4aEnlightenment. 4afamilies. 4aphilosophy. 4ascience. 4aself-fashioning. 4asentimentalism. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUChP eBook-Package 2014-2016z978311070422808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUChP eBook-Package 2016z978311068860308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018z978311063537940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226384252423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226384252.jpg  a978-3-11-063537-9  University of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-068860-3  UChP eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-070422-8  UChP eBook-Package 2014-2016c2014d2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles